text: Rutherford College is a public high school for 12-18 year old boys and girls in Te Atatu Peninsula, Auckland, New Zealand. Opened in 1961, it was named after the Nobel Prize winning nuclear physicist and chemist, Lord Ernest Rutherford, who was born in New Zealand.
